<paragraph id="B73836BB3412FF96FF5CC78A187790F5" blockId="9.[178,1086,636,741]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">
M a t e r i a l e x a m i n e d: 
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B3412FF96FE07C78A181590DE" box="[489,573,696,718]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Turkey</collectingCountry>
:13, 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FD88C78A18BF90DE" box="[614,663,696,718]" country="Turkey" name="Bitlis" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Bitlis</collectingRegion>
, Yelkenli, 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FD18C78A193390DD" box="[758,795,696,717]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Van</collectingRegion>
lake, 
<geoCoordinate id="D2B3507C3412FF96FCBFC78A19B390DD" box="[849,923,696,717]" degrees="38" direction="north" minutes="28" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" precision="925" value="38.466667">38°28'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="D2B3507C3412FF96FC4AC78A19C490DD" box="[932,1004,696,717]" degrees="42" direction="east" minutes="32" orientation="longitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" precision="925" value="42.533333">42°32'E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity id="707F9B5E3412FF96FC1BC78A1E1290DD" box="[1013,1082,696,717]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
, pitfall, 
<date id="C339107B3412FF96FEF0C7FD1B9290F4" box="[286,442,719,740]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" value="2014-04-21" valueMax="2014-05-20" valueMin="2014-04-21">21.IV.-20.V.2014</date>
, leg. Reuter (cFel).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FF9D65303412FF96FF5CC7C11BF996F5" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph id="B73836BB3412FF96FF5CC7C11BB19696" blockId="9.[178,1086,755,1158]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">
C o m m e n t: The 
<typeStatus id="683C88193412FF96FE7BC7C11BC69119" box="[405,494,755,777]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FDF2C7C618869118" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[540,686,755,777]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipennis">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FDF2C7C618869118" box="[540,686,755,777]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. luteipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was collected to the east of 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FF5CC6221B2B9136" box="[178,259,784,806]" country="Turkey" name="Kayseri" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Kayseri</collectingRegion>
, was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A3412FF96FE5FC623187E9137" author="ASSING V" box="[433,598,785,807]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref5676" refString="ASSING V. (2007 a): On the Xantholinini of Turkey and adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae). - Zootaxa 1474: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="2007">ASSING (2007a)</bibRefCitation>
, who recorded the species also from 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FC38C6221E149136" box="[982,1084,784,806]" country="Turkey" name="Gaziantep" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Gaziantep</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FF31C61C1B609154" box="[223,328,814,836]" country="Turkey" name="Adiyaman" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Adıyaman</collectingRegion>
provinces. According to the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FC8BC61C19D99153" authorityName="ANLAS" authorityYear="2014" box="[869,1009,814,835]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khachikovi">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FC8BC61C19D99153" box="[869,1009,814,835]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. khachikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is based on 
<specimenCount id="A181FD323412FF96FEC4C67E1BB99171" box="[298,401,843,865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="A181FD323412FF96FE2DC67E181A9171" box="[451,562,843,865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
from two localities in 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FCF7C67E198F9171" box="[793,935,843,865]" country="Turkey" name="Mus" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Muş province</collectingRegion>
, this species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FE92C65B1822916D" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[380,522,872,894]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipennis">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FE92C65B1822916D" box="[380,522,872,894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. luteipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the paler coloration of the head and pronotum, as well as by &quot;less dense and less numerous sclerotised spines in the aedeagus&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A3412FF96FC1BC6B41ACF91A9" author="ANLAS S" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref5554" refString="ANLAS S. (2014): On the genus Xantholinus DEJEAN of Turkey: three new species, new and additional records, with distributional checklist (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae: Xantholinini). - Journal of Insect Biodiversity 2 (11): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2014">ANLAŞ 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The coloration may be subject to enormous intraspecific variation in 
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FC5BC6911E1591A8" box="[949,1085,931,952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Helicophallus</emphasis>
species and is consequently of little taxonomic signifance. More importantly, the somewhat unclear photographs of the aedeagus (
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A3412FF96FD87C6EC18C691E3" author="ANLAS S" box="[617,750,990,1011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref5554" refString="ANLAS S. (2014): On the genus Xantholinus DEJEAN of Turkey: three new species, new and additional records, with distributional checklist (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae: Xantholinini). - Journal of Insect Biodiversity 2 (11): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2014">ANLAŞ 2014</bibRefCitation>
: figures 46-49) do not reveal any significant differences between the internal structures of the aedeagus of the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FF19C12B1BAA963D" authorityName="ANLAS" authorityYear="2014" box="[247,386,1048,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khachikovi">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FF19C12B1BAA963D" box="[247,386,1048,1070]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. khachikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and those of the 
<typeStatus id="683C88193412FF96FDDCC12A18A3963E" box="[562,651,1048,1070]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FD40C12B1912963D" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[686,826,1048,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipennis">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FD40C12B1912963D" box="[686,826,1048,1070]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. luteipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the number, shapes, and degree of sclerotization of the spines are practically identical, so that there is little doubt that the 
<typeStatus id="683C88193412FF96FEE6C1611B429679" box="[264,362,1107,1129]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FE7CC16118369678" authorityName="ANLAS" authorityYear="2014" box="[402,542,1107,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khachikovi">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FE7CC16118369678" box="[402,542,1107,1128]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. khachikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FDBAC16118C99678" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[596,737,1107,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipennis">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FDBAC16118C99678" box="[596,737,1107,1128]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. luteipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are conspecific. Hence the synonymy proposed above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B73836BB3412FF96FF5CC1A71BF996F5" blockId="9.[178,1085,1173,1254]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">
As can be inferred from the new records (
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FDB7C1A718BB96BB" box="[601,659,1173,1195]" country="Turkey" name="Bitlis" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Bitlis</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FD70C1A418E396BB" box="[670,715,1174,1195]" country="Turkey" name="Mus" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Muş</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383412FF96FD0EC1A4194496BA" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[736,876,1173,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipennis">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93412FF96FD0EC1A4194496BA" box="[736,876,1173,1195]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">X. luteipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is remarkably widespread in southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B3412FF96FE75C1801BDD96D8" box="[411,501,1202,1224]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, its currently known distribution ranging from 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FC3AC1801E0B96D8" box="[980,1059,1202,1224]" country="Turkey" name="Kayseri" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Kayseri</collectingRegion>
in the west to 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593412FF96FEC8C1E21B7596F6" box="[294,349,1232,1254]" country="Turkey" name="Bitlis" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Bitlis</collectingRegion>
in the east.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
